{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850117349,"sessionID":"ses_287179656ffezx7f2tbbaM7DVN","part":{"id":"prt_d78ea5877001aPUzZTMZnJd4ld","messageID":"msg_d78e8d975001sSE7hBywqPVwdu","sessionID":"ses_287179656ffezx7f2tbbaM7DVN","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-31ef831620b74dfda483c603a62dadea","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-010 Design - Router Session Management\n\n## Overview\n\nAR-010 enhances the Router module's session management capabilities by integrating the generated Kubernetes client-go library for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group. This integration enables the router to watch and cache AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources directly from the Kubernetes API server, reducing dependency on the workload manager HTTP API and improving reliability and performance.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  Kubernetes API Server                                      │\n│  - AgentRuntime CRD                                         │\n│  - CodeInterpreter CRD                                      │\n└────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                     │ Watch/Cache\n                     ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  client-go Informer Factory                                 │\n│  - AgentRuntimeInformer                                     │\n│  - CodeInterpreterInformer                                  │\n│  - AgentRuntimeLister                                       │\n│  - CodeInterpreterLister                                    │\n└────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                     │ Resource Events\n                     ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  Enhanced Session Manager                                   │\n│  - Resource State Sync                                      │\n│  - Event Handler                                            │\n│  - Cache Coordination                                       │\n└────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                     │\n           ┌─────────┴─────────┐\n           │                   │\n           ▼                   ▼\n┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐\n│  Redis Store     │  │  Workload Mgr    │\n│  - Session Cache │  │  - Fallback      │\n└──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Layered Architecture\n\n1. **Kubernetes API Layer**: client-go generated clients for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter\n2. **Cache Layer**: Informers and listers for local resource state\n3. **Session Management Layer**: Enhanced session manager with Kubernetes integration\n4. **Storage Layer**: Redis store for session data\n5. **Integration Layer**: Workload manager fallback for legacy operations\n\n### Key Components\n\n#### Enhanced Session Manager (`session_manager.go`)\n\n```go\ntype SessionManager interface {\n    GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    CreateSession(ctx context.Context, name string, namespace string, kind string) (string, *types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    DeleteSession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    ListSessions(ctx context.Context) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n}\n\ntype manager struct {\n    storeClient         store.Store\n    workloadMgrAddr     string\n    httpClient          *http.Client\n\n    // Kubernetes client integration\n    agentRuntimeLister  runtimev1alpha1listers.AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n    codeInterpreterLister runtimev1alpha1listers.CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister\n    informerFactory     informers.SharedInformerFactory\n\n    // Resource state cache\n    resourceCache       *ResourceCache\n}\n```\n\n**Responsibilities:**\n- Session-based sandbox lookup with Kubernetes resource cache\n- Resource state synchronization using informers\n- Cache coordination between Kubernetes and Redis\n- Workload manager fallback for session creation\n- Event-driven updates from Kubernetes\n\n#### Resource Cache (`resource_cache.go`)\n\n```go\ntype ResourceCache struct {\n    mu         sync.RWMutex\n    agentRuntimes map[string]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime\n    codeInterpreters map[string]*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter\n}\n\nfunc (rc *ResourceCache) GetAgentRuntime(namespace, name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\nfunc (rc *ResourceCache) GetCodeInterpreter(namespace, name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\nfunc (rc *ResourceCache) UpdateAgentRuntime(ar *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\nfunc (rc *ResourceCache) UpdateCodeInterpreter(ci *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter)\nfunc (rc *ResourceCache) DeleteAgentRuntime(namespace, name string)\nfunc (rc *ResourceCache) DeleteCodeInterpreter(namespace, name string)\n```\n\n**Responsibilities:**\n- Thread-safe in-memory cache of Kubernetes resources\n- Event-driven updates from informers\n- Fast resource lookup without API server calls\n- Cache invalidation on resource deletion\n\n#### Informer Manager (`informer_manager.go`)\n\n```go\ntype InformerManager struct {\n    clientset           *agentcubeclient.Clientset\n    informerFactory     informers.SharedInformerFactory\n    agentRuntimeInformer cache.SharedIndexInformer\n    codeInterpreterInformer cache.SharedIndexInformer\n    resourceCache       *ResourceCache\n}\n\nfunc NewInformerManager(clientset *agentcubeclient.Clientset, resyncPeriod time.Duration) (*InformerManager, error)\nfunc (im *InformerManager) Start(stopCh <-chan struct{})\nfunc (im *InformerManager) WaitForCacheSync(stopCh <-chan struct{}) bool\nfunc (im *InformerManager) GetAgentRuntimeLister() runtimev1alpha1listers.AgentRuntimeLister\nfunc (im *InformerManager) GetCodeInterpreterLister() runtimev1alpha1listers.CodeInterpreterLister\n```\n\n**Responsibilities:**\n- Informer factory initialization\n- Event handler registration\n- Cache synchronization management\n- Graceful shutdown handling\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Resource Cache Entry\n\n```go\ntype ResourceCacheEntry struct {\n    Resource    interface{}\n    Version     string\n    Timestamp   time.Time\n}\n```\n\n### Session Metadata\n\n```go\ntype SessionMetadata struct {\n    SessionID        string\n    Namespace        string\n    Name             string\n    Kind             string\n    ResourceVersion  string\n    CreatedAt        time.Time\n    LastUpdated      time.Time\n}\n```\n\n### Resource State\n\n```go\ntype ResourceState struct {\n    Namespace        string\n    Name             string\n    Kind             string\n    Ready            bool\n    Conditions       []metav1.Condition\n    ObservedGeneration int64\n    LastTransitionTime time.Time\n}\n```\n\n### Kubernetes Resource Mapping\n\n```go\nfunc SandboxInfoFromAgentRuntime(ar *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, sessionID string) *types.SandboxInfo {\n    return &types.SandboxInfo{\n        Kind:             types.AgentRuntimeKind,\n        Name:             ar.Name,\n        Namespace:        ar.Namespace,\n        SandboxName:      getSandboxPodName(ar),\n        SandboxNamespace: ar.Namespace,\n        Status:           getResourceStatus(ar.Status.Conditions),\n        CreatedAt:        ar.CreationTimestamp.Time,\n        ExpiresAt:        getExpirationTime(ar),\n        // ... additional fields\n    }\n}\n\nfunc SandboxInfoFromCodeInterpreter(ci *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, sessionID string) *types.SandboxInfo {\n    return &types.SandboxInfo{\n        Kind:             types.CodeInterpreterKind,\n        Name:             ci.Name,\n        Namespace:        ci.Namespace,\n        SandboxName:      getSandboxPodName(ci),\n        SandboxNamespace: ci.Namespace,\n        Status:           getResourceStatus(ci.Status.Conditions),\n        CreatedAt:        ci.CreationTimestamp.Time,\n        ExpiresAt:        getExpirationTime(ci),\n        // ... additional fields\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Kubernetes Client Integration\n\n#### Clientset Initialization\n\n```go\nfunc InitializeAgentcubeClient(config *rest.Config) (*agentcubeclient.Clientset, error) {\n    clientset, err := agentcubeclient.NewForConfig(config)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create agentcube clientset: %w\", err)\n    }\n    return clientset, nil\n}\n```\n\n#### Informer Setup\n\n```go\nfunc SetupInformers(clientset *agentcubeclient.Clientset, namespace string, resyncPeriod time.Duration) (*InformerManager, error) {\n    factory := agentcubeinformers.NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(\n        clientset,\n        resyncPeriod,\n        agentcubeinformers.WithNamespace(namespace),\n    )\n\n    informerManager := &InformerManager{\n        clientset:       clientset,\n        informerFactory: factory,\n        resourceCache:   NewResourceCache(),\n    }\n\n    agentRuntimeInformer := factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()\n    codeInterpreterInformer := factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters().Informer()\n\n    agentRuntimeInformer.AddEventHandler(cache.ResourceEventHandlerFuncs{\n        AddFunc:    informerManager.handleAgentRuntimeAdd,\n        UpdateFunc: informerManager.handleAgentRuntimeUpdate,\n        DeleteFunc: informerManager.handleAgentRuntimeDelete,\n    })\n\n    codeInterpreterInformer.AddEventHandler(cache.ResourceEventHandlerFuncs{\n        AddFunc:    informerManager.handleCodeInterpreterAdd,\n        UpdateFunc: informerManager.handleCodeInterpreterUpdate,\n        DeleteFunc: informerManager.handleCodeInterpreterDelete,\n    })\n\n    informerManager.agentRuntimeInformer = agentRuntimeInformer\n    informerManager.codeInterpreterInformer = codeInterpreterInformer\n\n    return informerManager, nil\n}\n```\n\n### Enhanced Session Manager API\n\n#### Get Sandbox by Session (Enhanced)\n\n```go\nfunc (m *manager) GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n    // Try Redis cache first\n    sandboxInfo, err := m.storeClient.GetSandbox(ctx, sessionID)\n    if err == nil {\n        // Verify resource is still active in Kubernetes\n        if m.isResourceActive(namespace, name, kind) {\n            klog.V(4).Infof(\"Cache hit for session: %s\", sessionID)\n            return sandboxInfo, nil\n        }\n        // Resource is deleted or not ready, remove from cache\n        m.storeClient.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n    }\n\n    if err != store.ErrNotFound {\n        klog.Warningf(\"Failed to get sandbox from store: %v\", err)\n    }\n\n    // Try Kubernetes resource cache\n    if kind == types.AgentRuntimeKind {\n        ar, err := m.agentRuntimeLister.AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(name)\n        if err == nil {\n            return m.buildSandboxInfoFromAgentRuntime(ar, sessionID)\n        }\n    } else if kind == types.CodeInterpreterKind {\n        ci, err := m.codeInterpreterLister.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Get(name)\n        if err == nil {\n            return m.buildSandboxInfoFromCodeInterpreter(ci, sessionID)\n        }\n    }\n\n    // Fallback to workload manager\n    klog.V(4).Infof(\"Kubernetes cache miss, querying workload manager for session: %s\", sessionID)\n    return m.getSandboxFromWorkloadManager(ctx, sessionID)\n}\n```\n\n#### Create Session (Enhanced)\n\n```go\nfunc (m *manager) CreateSession(ctx context.Context, name string, namespace string, kind string) (string, *types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n    // Validate request\n    if err := validateKind(kind); err != nil {\n        return \"\", nil, err\n    }\n\n    if !isValidNamespace(namespace) {\n        return \"\", nil, &ValidationError{Field: \"namespace\", Message: \"invalid namespace format\"}\n    }\n\n    if !isValidResourceName(name) {\n        return \"\", nil, &ValidationError{Field: \"name\", Message: \"invalid resource name format\"}\n    }\n\n    // Check if resource exists in Kubernetes\n    if kind == types.AgentRuntimeKind {\n        ar, err := m.agentRuntimeLister.AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(name)\n        if err == nil && isResourceReady(ar.Status.Conditions) {\n            // Resource exists and is ready, create session directly\n            sessionID := uuid.New().String()\n            sandboxInfo := m.buildSandboxInfoFromAgentRuntime(ar, sessionID)\n            if err := m.storeClient.StoreSandbox(ctx, sessionID, sandboxInfo); err != nil {\n                klog.Warningf(\"Failed to cache sandbox info: %v\", err)\n            }\n            return sessionID, sandboxInfo, nil\n        }\n    } else if kind == types.CodeInterpreterKind {\n        ci, err := m.codeInterpreterLister.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Get(name)\n        if err == nil && ci.Status.Ready {\n            // Resource exists and is ready, create session directly\n            sessionID := uuid.New().String()\n            sandboxInfo := m.buildSandboxInfoFromCodeInterpreter(ci, sessionID)\n            if err := m.storeClient.StoreSandbox(ctx, sessionID, sandboxInfo); err != nil {\n                klog.Warningf(\"Failed to cache sandbox info: %v\", err)\n            }\n            return sessionID, sandboxInfo, nil\n        }\n    }\n\n    // Fallback to workload manager for resource creation\n    return m.createSessionViaWorkloadManager(ctx, name, namespace, kind)\n}\n```\n\n#### Delete Session\n\n```go\nfunc (m *manager) DeleteSession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error {\n    // Remove from Redis store\n    if err := m.storeClient.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID); err != nil {\n        klog.Warningf(\"Failed to delete session from store: %v\", err)\n    }\n\n    // Notify workload manager\n    endpoint := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/v1/session/%s\", m.workloadMgrAddr, sessionID)\n    req, err := http.NewRequestWithContext(ctx, http.MethodDelete, endpoint, nil)\n    if err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create request: %w\", err)\n    }\n\n    resp, err := m.httpClient.Do(req)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Warningf(\"Failed to notify workload manager: %v\", err)\n        return nil\n    }\n    defer resp.Body.Close()\n\n    if resp.StatusCode != http.StatusOK && resp.StatusCode != http.StatusNotFound {\n        klog.Warningf(\"Workload manager returned status: %d\", resp.StatusCode)\n    }\n\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### Event Handlers\n\n```go\nfunc (im *InformerManager) handleAgentRuntimeAdd(obj interface{}) {\n    ar := obj.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n    klog.Infof(\"AgentRuntime added: %s/%s\", ar.Namespace, ar.Name)\n    im.resourceCache.UpdateAgentRuntime(ar)\n}\n\nfunc (im *InformerManager) handleAgentRuntimeUpdate(oldObj, newObj interface{}) {\n    oldAR := oldObj.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n    newAR := newObj.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n\n    if oldAR.ResourceVersion == newAR.ResourceVersion {\n        return\n    }\n\n    klog.Infof(\"AgentRuntime updated: %s/%s (version: %s)\", newAR.Namespace, newAR.Name, newAR.ResourceVersion)\n    im.resourceCache.UpdateAgentRuntime(newAR)\n\n    // Trigger session cache invalidation if conditions changed\n    if conditionsChanged(oldAR.Status.Conditions, newAR.Status.Conditions) {\n        im.invalidateSessionsForResource(newAR.Namespace, newAR.Name, types.AgentRuntimeKind)\n    }\n}\n\nfunc (im *InformerManager) handleAgentRuntimeDelete(obj interface{}) {\n    ar := obj.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n    klog.Infof(\"AgentRuntime deleted: %s/%s\", ar.Namespace, ar.Name)\n    im.resourceCache.DeleteAgentRuntime(ar.Namespace, ar.Name)\n    im.invalidateSessionsForResource(ar.Namespace, ar.Name, types.AgentRuntimeKind)\n}\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Types\n\n1. **Kubernetes API Errors** (5xx)\n   - Informer synchronization failures\n   - Lister retrieval errors\n   - Cache synchronization timeouts\n\n2. **Resource Not Found Errors** (404)\n   - AgentRuntime resource not found\n   - CodeInterpreter resource not found\n   - Session not found\n\n3. **Validation Errors** (400)\n   - Invalid resource kind\n   - Missing required parameters\n   - Invalid namespace or name format\n\n4. **Resource State Errors** (503)\n   - Resource not ready\n   - Resource conditions failed\n   - Resource deletion in progress\n\n5. **Fallback Errors**\n   - Workload manager communication failures\n   - Redis store access failures\n   - Partial degradation scenarios\n\n### Error Handling Strategy\n\n1. **Graceful Degradation**\n   - Use Kubernetes cache when available\n   - Fallback to workload manager for missing resources\n   - Return cached data if API server is temporarily unavailable\n\n2. **Cache Invalidation**\n   - Automatic invalidation on resource deletion\n   - Conditional invalidation on status changes\n   - Manual invalidation for critical updates\n\n3. **Circuit Breaker Pattern**\n   - Limit retries to Kubernetes API\n   - Fail fast after consecutive failures\n   - Automatic recovery after successful sync\n\n4. **Context Propagation**\n   - Propagate context timeouts to informers\n   - Respect cache sync deadlines\n   - Clean up resources on cancellation\n\n5. **Logging and Metrics**\n   - Log all cache misses and hits\n   - Track informer sync latency\n   - Monitor resource state transitions\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n#### Resource Cache Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestResourceCache_GetAgentRuntime(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestResourceCache_GetCodeInterpreter(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestResourceCache_UpdateAgentRuntime(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestResourceCache_UpdateCodeInterpreter(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestResourceCache_DeleteAgentRuntime(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestResourceCache_DeleteCodeInterpreter(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestResourceCache_ConcurrentAccess(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n**Coverage:**\n- Cache get/update/delete operations\n- Concurrent access safety\n- Thread safety guarantees\n\n#### Informer Manager Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestInformerManager_Start(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestInformerManager_WaitForCacheSync(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestInformerManager_handleAgentRuntimeAdd(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestInformerManager_handleAgentRuntimeUpdate(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestInformerManager_handleAgentRuntimeDelete(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestInformerManager_handleCodeInterpreterAdd(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestInformerManager_handleCodeInterpreterUpdate(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestInformerManager_handleCodeInterpreterDelete(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n**Coverage:**\n- Informer lifecycle management\n- Event handling\n- Cache synchronization\n\n#### Enhanced Session Manager Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession_KubernetesCache(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession_RedisCache(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession_WorkloadManagerFallback(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSessionManager_CreateSession_KubernetesResource(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSessionManager_CreateSession_WorkloadManagerFallback(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSessionManager_DeleteSession(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSessionManager_ListSessions(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n**Coverage:**\n- Cache hierarchy (Kubernetes → Redis → Workload Manager)\n- Resource state validation\n- Session lifecycle management\n- Error handling\n\n#### Resource Mapping Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestSandboxInfoFromAgentRuntime(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSandboxInfoFromCodeInterpreter(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestGetResourceStatus(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestGetExpirationTime(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestIsResourceReady(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestConditionsChanged(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n**Coverage:**\n- Resource to sandbox info mapping\n- Condition parsing\n- Expiration time calculation\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n#### Kubernetes Integration Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestKubernetesIntegration_AgentRuntimeCRUD(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestKubernetesIntegration_CodeInterpreterCRUD(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestKubernetesIntegration_InformerSync(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestKubernetesIntegration_ResourceWatch(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestKubernetesIntegration_SessionCacheInvalidation(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n**Setup:**\n- Kind cluster or test Kubernetes cluster\n- Installed AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs\n- Test clientset configuration\n\n**Coverage:**\n- End-to-end Kubernetes integration\n- Informer synchronization\n- Event propagation\n- Cache invalidation\n\n#### End-to-End Session Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestE2E_SessionCreationWithKubernetesResource(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestE2E_SessionCreationWithWorkloadManager(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestE2E_SessionRetrievalFromCache(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestE2E_SessionDeletion(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestE2E_ResourceDeletionSessionInvalidation(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n**Coverage:**\n- Complete session lifecycle\n- Cache fallback behavior\n- Resource state synchronization\n\n### Performance Tests\n\n```go\nfunc BenchmarkResourceCache_GetAgentRuntime(b *testing.B)\nfunc BenchmarkResourceCache_UpdateAgentRuntime(b *testing.B)\nfunc BenchmarkInformerManager_EventHandling(b *testing.B)\nfunc BenchmarkSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession(b *testing.B)\n```\n\n**Metrics:**\n- Cache lookup latency\n- Event processing throughput\n- Memory usage\n- Goroutine count\n\n### Load Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestLoad_ConcurrentSessionAccess(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestLoad_HighEventRate(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestLoad_MixedCacheHitsAndMisses(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n**Scenarios:**\n- High concurrency\n- Rapid resource updates\n- Mixed cache hit/miss patterns\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### Authentication\n\n1. **Kubernetes Service Account**\n   - In-cluster authentication\n   - RBAC configuration for resource access\n   - Minimal privilege principle\n\n2. **Client Configuration**\n   - Secure config loading\n   - Certificate validation\n   - TLS verification\n\n### Authorization\n\n1. **RBAC Rules**\n   - Read-only access to AgentRuntime resources\n   - Read-only access to CodeInterpreter resources\n   - Namespace-scoped access\n\n2. **Resource Access Control**\n   - Namespace isolation\n   - Resource name validation\n   - Kind-based routing\n\n### Data Protection\n\n1. **Sensitive Data**\n   - No sensitive data in resource cache\n   - Session data stored in encrypted Redis\n   - Secure key management\n\n2. **Cache Security**\n   - Memory-only resource cache\n   - No persistence of sensitive data\n   - Regular cache cleanup\n\n## Performance Optimizations\n\n### Caching Strategy\n\n1. **Three-Tier Cache**\n   - L1: Kubernetes informer cache (in-memory, auto-synced)\n   - L2: Redis store (persistent, TTL-based)\n   - L3: Workload manager (fallback, HTTP-based)\n\n2. **Cache Warmup**\n   - Pre-load existing resources on startup\n   - Sync informers before serving requests\n   - Populate Redis cache with active sessions\n\n3. **Cache Invalidation**\n   - Event-driven invalidation\n   - TTL-based expiration\n   - Manual invalidation for critical updates\n\n### Resource Management\n\n1. **Informer Optimization**\n   - Configurable resync period\n   - Namespace-scoped informers\n   - Efficient event filtering\n\n2. **Memory Management**\n   - Bounded cache size\n   - LRU eviction policy\n   - Regular cleanup of stale entries\n\n3. **Connection Management**\n   - Connection pooling for Kubernetes API\n   - Keep-alive connections\n   - Efficient HTTP client usage\n\n### Request Processing\n\n1. **Fast Path**\n   - Kubernetes cache lookup (microsecond latency)\n   - In-memory cache access\n   - No network calls for cached resources\n\n2. **Slow Path**\n   - Redis cache lookup (millisecond latency)\n   - Workload manager fallback (tens of milliseconds)\n   - Graceful degradation on failures\n\n## Monitoring and Observability\n\n### Metrics\n\n1. **Kubernetes Integration Metrics**\n   - Informer sync status\n   - Cache hit/miss rate\n   - Event processing latency\n   - Resource count per namespace\n\n2. **Session Metrics**\n   - Active sessions\n   - Session creation rate\n   - Session deletion rate\n   - Cache hit rate by tier\n\n3. **Performance Metrics**\n   - Cache lookup latency (p50, p95, p99)\n   - Informer event processing time\n   - Resource state transition time\n\n### Logging\n\n1. **Structured Logging**\n   - Resource events (add/update/delete)\n   - Cache operations (hit/miss/invalidation)\n   - Session lifecycle events\n   - Error conditions with context\n\n2. **Log Levels**\n   - Debug: Detailed cache operations\n   - Info: Resource state changes\n   - Warning: Cache misses and fallbacks\n   - Error: Failures and exceptions\n\n### Health Checks\n\n1. **Informer Sync Status**\n   - Check if informers have synced\n   - Verify cache is populated\n   - Report sync status in readiness probe\n\n2. **Resource Availability**\n   - Check if critical resources exist\n   - Verify resource state\n   - Report availability in health check\n\n## Deployment\n\n### Configuration\n\n**Environment Variables:**\n- `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE`: Router namespace (default: `default`)\n- `INFORMER_RESYNC_PERIOD`: Informer resync period (default: `10m`)\n- `CACHE_WARMUP_ENABLED`: Enable cache warmup (default: `true`)\n- `CACHE_WARMUP_TIMEOUT`: Cache warmup timeout (default: `30s`)\n\n**CLI Flags:**\n- `--informer-namespace`: Namespace to watch (default: all namespaces)\n- `--informer-resync-period`: Informer resync period\n- `--enable-kubernetes-cache`: Enable Kubernetes cache (default: `true`)\n\n### Kubernetes Deployment\n\n**Deployment Manifest:**\n```yaml\napiVersion: apps/v1\nkind: Deployment\nmetadata:\n  name: agentcube-router\nspec:\n  replicas: 3\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: agentcube-router\n  template:\n    metadata:\n      labels:\n        app: agentcube-router\n    spec:\n      serviceAccountName: agentcube-router\n      containers:\n      - name: router\n        image: volcano-sh/agentcube-router:latest\n        ports:\n        - containerPort: 8080\n        env:\n        - name: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n          value: \"http://agentcube-workload-manager:8081\"\n        - name: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\n          value: \"default\"\n        - name: INFORMER_RESYNC_PERIOD\n          value: \"10m\"\n        - name: ENABLE_KUBERNETES_CACHE\n          value: \"true\"\n        livenessProbe:\n          httpGet:\n            path: /health/live\n            port: 8080\n        readinessProbe:\n          httpGet:\n            path: /health/ready\n            port: 8080\n          initialDelaySeconds: 5\n          periodSeconds: 10\n```\n\n**RBAC Manifest:**\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ServiceAccount\nmetadata:\n  name: agentcube-router\n  namespace: default\n---\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: Role\nmetadata:\n  name: agentcube-router\n  namespace: default\nrules:\n- apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n  resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"agentruntimes/status\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n  resources: [\"codeinterpreters\", \"codeinterpreters/status\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n---\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: RoleBinding\nmetadata:\n  name: agentcube-router\n  namespace: default\nsubjects:\n- kind: ServiceAccount\n  name: agentcube-router\n  namespace: default\nroleRef:\n  kind: Role\n  name: agentcube-router\n  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n```\n\n### Scalability\n\n1. **Horizontal Scaling**\n   - Stateless informer instances\n   - Each replica maintains own cache\n   - Load balancer distribution\n\n2. **Vertical Scaling**\n   - Configurable cache sizes\n   - Memory-based resource limits\n   - CPU allocation for event processing\n\n## Future Enhancements\n\n1. **Multi-Cluster Support**\n   - Watch resources across multiple clusters\n   - Federation of session state\n   - Cross-cluster failover\n\n2. **Advanced Caching**\n   - Predictive cache preloading\n   - Machine learning-based cache optimization\n   - Adaptive TTL based on access patterns\n\n3. **Event Streaming**\n   - Integration with event streaming platforms\n   - Real-time session state propagation\n   - Pub/sub for session events\n\n4. **Performance Improvements**\n   - Cache sharding for large deployments\n   - Compression for cache data\n   - Zero-copy optimizations\n\n5. **Observability Enhancements**\n   - Distributed tracing integration\n   - Prometheus metrics export\n   - Grafana dashboard templates\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Runtime Dependencies\n\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`: Generated Kubernetes client\n- `k8s.io/client-go`: Kubernetes client library\n- `k8s.io/apimachinery`: Kubernetes API machinery\n- `k8s.io/klog/v2`: Logging\n- `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`: Redis client\n- `github.com/gin-gonic/gin`: HTTP framework\n\n### Internal Dependencies\n\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`: Store interface\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types`: Common types\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`: API types\n\n## References\n\n- [Kubernetes client-go Documentation](https://github.com/kubernetes/client-go)\n- [Kubernetes Informer Pattern](https://github.com/kubernetes/client-go/blob/master/tools/cache/controller.go)\n- [Kubernetes API Conventions](https://github.com/kubernetes/community/blob/master/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md)\n- [Agentcube API Specification](../deployment/client-go.md)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-010/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/controller.go\">\nERROR [57:3] unknown field MetricsBindAddress in struct literal of type controllerruntime.Options\nERROR [58:3] unknown field Port in struct literal of type controllerruntime.Options\nERROR [62:3] unknown field SyncPeriod in struct literal of type controllerruntime.Options\nERROR [88:17] undefin